-- Gold Ratio to Silver Falls Below 60 for the First Time Since October 2009
-- B y   G l e n y s   S i m
-- 2010-09-29T02:20:27Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-29/gold-ratio-to-silver-falls-below-60-for-the-first-time-since-october-2009.html
The ratio of gold to silver dropped
below 60 for the first time in 11 months as investors sought a
protection of wealth in the metal that may also benefit from
economic growth. One ounce of gold bought as little as 59.9787
ounces of silver today, the least since October last year.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Glenys Sim at 
 gsim4@bloomberg.net  